pregnancy weight i am weeks prengnat and was told to gain a pound a week with my baby i have been doing so until this week i lost pounds i have been have a lot of morning sickness but no puking and i've been eating a lot lately i weighed last week and this week whats going on you shouldn't really start gaining a pound a week until closer to weeks in your first trimester you should gain about lbs total or less if you are oveerweight to begin a little more if you were underweight to begin i was a normal average weight when i found out i was pregnant and at my last appointment weeks i had only gained about ounces so far just over half a pound my doctor said i was doing great but she expected me to start gaining about pound to a pound a week over these next couple of weeks i am now weeks and have gained about pounds all together so she was dead on good luck they say not to worry if you lose weight that first trimester if you have sever morning sickness unless you lose a lot of weight and are unable to get any nutrients into your body if thats the case talk to your doctor soemthign to help with morning sickness is eat something every hours even if your not hungry i never got any morning sickness from doing this if i felt a little nausious i would just eat something and elt fine afterward good luck to you hope this helps toni lynne Pregnancy Obstetrics Pound Adjustable gastric band Dieting Breastfeeding Binge eating disorder Super Size Me Abortion debate The Contender (television series) Roe v. Wade EastEnders Abortion in the United States Anorexia nervosa Piccolo Junior Saga Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Premature birth Fasting Hyperemesis gravidarum Sharon Tate Atkins Nutritional Approach Morning sickness Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Childbirth Intact dilation and extraction Good Morning, Vietnam Guinea pig Effect of Hurricane Katrina on New Orleans Abortion Terri Schiavo Cephalic disorder Days of our Lives Body mass index One Piece minor characters Phoebe Halliwell Mel